snippet: The major-label debut for the Weeknd (Abel Tesfaye) is pulpy, mournful and unnerving, with plenty of songs about the cheap thrills and unstructured lust of life on tour.
abstract: Jon Caramanica Critic's Notebook on Kiss Land, major-label debut for the Weeknd (Abel Tesfaye); calls album pulpy, mournful and unnerving, with plenty of songs about cheap thrills and unstructured lust of life on tour.
